## Card Pattern (the defining visual)
```tsx
<div
  className="rounded-2xl border-[2.5px] border-[#0a0a1a] overflow-hidden"
  style={{ background: "#fffbf0", boxShadow: "4px 4px 0 #0a0a1a" }}
>
  {/* Entity left stripe */}
  <div className="w-1 h-full" style={{ background: entityColor }} />
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

**Press-down effect on interactive cards:**
```tsx
className="transition-all active:translate-x-[2px] active:translate-y-[2px] active:shadow-none"
```

## Shadow Scale
- Cards:    `4px 4px 0 #0a0a1a`
- Buttons:  `3px 3px 0 #0a0a1a`
- Tags:     `2px 2px 0 #0a0a1a`
- Small:    `1px 1px 0 #0a0a1a`

## Typography
- Section headers: `Orbitron, font-black, uppercase, tracking-widest, 11px`
- Stat numbers:    `Orbitron, font-black, text-2xl+`
- Body:            `Inter, text-sm, text-[#0a0a1a]`
- Labels/tags:     `Orbitron, font-black, 9–10px, uppercase`

## PixelIcon Available Names
home, target, quill, pencil, building, trophy, pipeline, alert, clock,
dollar, chart, rocket, search, check, arrow_left, arrow_right, bell,
refresh, filter, star, cross

**Writing tab always uses `quill`, not `pencil`.**

## Routing
- `/pipeline?stage=submitted`  → Pipeline pre-filtered to Submitted stage
- `/pipeline?stage=writing`    → Pipeline pre-filtered to Writing/Review stage
- `/pipeline?pillar=…`         → Pipeline pre-filtered by pillar name
- `/opportunity/[id]`          → Full detail + inline edit for every field

## API Routes
- `GET /api/opportunities?status=…&pillar=…&priority=…`
- `GET /api/opportunities/[id]`
- `PATCH /api/opportunities/[id]` — body: `{ fields: { FieldName: value } }`
- `GET /api/stats`
- `GET /api/funders`

## Inline Field Editing
Use `<FieldEditor>` from `@/components/opportunity/FieldEditor` for any editable field.
Supported types: text, textarea, number, date, url, select.
Always PATCH to `/api/opportunities/[id]`.

## Bottom Nav
5 items: HQ (/), PIPELINE (/pipeline), WRITING (/writing-queue), FUNDERS (/funders), WINS (/awards)
Rainbow pixel stripe at top of nav bar.

## Do NOT
- Use emojis anywhere
- Use lucide-react icons
- Use dark backgrounds (#0a0a0a, #1a1a1a, etc.)
- Use gradient text (causes readability issues)
- Hardcode Airtable API keys (use env vars via lib/airtable.ts)
